item.title: Need help with portforward (PW)
item.dc:creator: @Volrom Volrom
item.description:
@Volrom wrote:

Ok listen:

Since you are using a desktop, just type in on your browser: 198.168.0.1, and you should come across a page saying NETGEAR and such. Go to the port forwarding section somewhere on the left. Just add a new service and name it, and for the starting/ending ports: 43594 and put in your ip address. You can go into command prompt and type ipconfig for your ip info. Then go to no-ip.org, register, create a new host, and name it yourserver.no-ip.org or something like that. And within 10min, startup your server on your desktop, then log into it using a client and the yourserver.no-ip.org.

Please +rep me if this was useful!

-Volrom
